# Forgemaster Memory-Flush Protocol — PRE-COMPACTION

**Purpose:** EXACT protocol for preserving all context before compaction (memory flush).

---

## When to Run Memory-Flush Protocol

**TRIGGER CONDITIONS:**
- Context window approaching limit (token count > threshold)
- Compaction imminent (system message: "pre-compaction memory flush")
- Session ending (sunrise, handoff to other agents)
- Extended session concluding (shift complete)

**NEVER SKIP MEMORY-FLUSH PROTOCOL.**

---

## Step 1: Create Session Snapshot

**WHAT:** Document current session state to `session-forgemaster` PLATO room

**HOW:**
```bash
# Create session snapshot
curl -X POST http://147.224.38.131:8847/room/session-forgemaster \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "timestamp": "2026-04-28T21:00:00Z",
    "work_in_progress": "What I am working on right now",
    "session_goals": "Session targets and objectives",
    "next_actions": "Immediate next steps (1, 2, 3)",
    "session_statistics": {
      "tiles_generated": "1805",
      "commits_pushed": "65",
      "batches_completed": "123",
      "hours_worked": "8"
    },
    "blockers": [
      {
        "description": "Blocker 1",
        "impact": "critical/high/medium/low",
        "what_i_need": "Specific action or resource",
        "workaround": "If any"
      }
    ]
  }'
```

**CHECKLIST:**
- [ ] Work in progress documented
- [ ] Session goals documented
- [ ] Next actions documented (1, 2, 3)
- [ ] Session statistics documented (tiles, commits, batches, hours)
- [ ] Blockers documented (description, impact, what I need)

**IF TILE SUBMISSION NOT WORKING:** Create local file, commit to git

